WEBVTT

00:00:01.345 --> 00:00:08.149
Your wallet remembers what happened. WhyTx remembers why, with private context
and verifiable onchain proof.

00:00:08.349 --> 00:00:16.580
Connection is non-custodial through Reown AppKit. Here I choose the isolated
WhyTx demo wallet.

00:00:16.780 --> 00:00:25.137
A gas-free signature unlocks the encrypted local ledger. It does not create a
transaction or expose the private notes.

00:00:25.337 --> 00:00:31.170
Monad Mainnet is the default network. Testnet remains available from the
network selector.

00:00:31.370 --> 00:00:39.408
I will document the real WhyTx registry deployment transaction already
confirmed on Monad Mainnet.

00:00:39.608 --> 00:00:46.965
WhyTx adds human context: purpose, category, counterparty, follow-up date,
status, and private details.

00:00:47.165 --> 00:00:59.073
Securing sends only a salted Merkle root to the WhyTx registry on Monad
Mainnet. The readable note stays encrypted in this browser.

00:00:59.273 --> 00:01:05.553
The overview now shows one secured record, one active follow-up, and no
unprotected draft.

00:01:05.753 --> 00:01:15.319
Transactions shows the complete ledger. Follow-ups isolates unresolved records
with a future action date.

00:01:15.519 --> 00:01:24.899
Shared Proofs contains secured records. I choose exactly which fields another
person may verify.

00:01:25.099 --> 00:01:33.802
The verification link exposes only selected fields, with proofs that they
match the earlier mainnet commitment.

00:01:34.002 --> 00:01:44.958
After a refresh, the current tab restores its session securely, so the wallet
does not ask for the same unlock signature again.

00:01:45.158 --> 00:01:55.063
Edits never overwrite history. This update becomes version two and links back
to the original secured record.

00:01:55.263 --> 00:02:02.143
The reveal screen now shows both secured versions, while the latest record
remains selectively shareable.

00:02:02.343 --> 00:02:13.673
Users can switch to Monad Testnet for testing, then return to Mainnet without
mixing transaction data or proof addresses.

00:02:13.873 --> 00:02:22.194
WhyTx completes one focused loop: attach, remember, follow up, reveal, and
independently verify why a crypto transaction happened.
